Package org.neo4j.kernel.impl.newapi

Class Operations

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.kernel.impl.newapi.Operations
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SchemaWrite, Write
    public class Operations
extends Object
implements Write, SchemaWrite
    Collects all Kernel API operations and guards them from being used outside of transaction. Many methods assume cursors to be initialized before use in private methods, even if they're not passed in explicitly. Keep that in mind: e.g. nodeCursor, propertyCursor and relationshipCursor

      • nodeCreateWithLabels

        public long nodeCreateWithLabels​(int[] labels)
                          throws ConstraintValidationException
        Description copied from interface: Write
        Create a node, and assign it the given array of labels.

        This method differs from a Write.nodeCreate() and Write.nodeAddLabel(long, int) sequence, in that we will avoid taking the "unlabelled node lock" of the nodeCreate, and we will avoid taking the exclusive node lock in the nodeAddLabel method.

        Specified by:
        nodeCreateWithLabels in interface Write
        Parameters:
        labels - The labels to assign to the newly created node.
        Returns:
        The internal id of the created node.
        Throws:
        ConstraintValidationException
